data.name: Espeon
data.flavorText: It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its enemy's actions.

data.name: Forretress
data.flavorText: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside the armor is a total mystery.

data.name: Hitmontop
data.flavorText: If you become enchanted by its smooth, elegant, dancelike kicks, you may get drilled hard.

data.name: Houndoom
data.flavorText: Upon hearing its eerie howls, other Pokémon get the shivers and head straight back to their nests.

data.name: Houndour
data.flavorText: To corner prey, they check each other's location using barks that only they can understand.

data.name: Kabutops
data.flavorText: In the water, it tucks its limbs to become more compact, then it wiggles its shell to swim fast.

data.name: Magnemite
data.flavorText: These Pokémon are attracted to electrical emissions and will often follow people using PokéGear.

data.name: Politoed
data.flavorText: Whenever three or more of these get together, they sing in a loud voice that sounds like bellowing.

data.name: Poliwrath
data.flavorText: Although an energetic, skilled swimmer that uses all of its muscles, it lives on dry land.

data.name: Scizor
data.flavorText: It swings its eye patterned pincers up to scare its foes. This makes it look like it has three heads.

data.name: Smeargle
data.flavorText: A special fluid oozes from the tip of its tail. It paints the fluid everywhere to mark its territory.

data.name: Tyranitar
data.flavorText: Its body can't be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.

data.name: Umbreon
data.flavorText: When darkness falls, the rings on the body begin to glow, striking fear in the hearts of anyone nearby.

data.name: Unown [A]
data.flavorText: Their shapes look like hieroglyphs on ancient tablets. It is said that the two are somehow related.

data.name: Ursaring
data.flavorText: Although it is a good climber, it prefers to snap trees with its forelegs and eat fallen berries.

data.name: Wobbuffet
data.flavorText: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

data.name: Yanma
data.flavorText: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

data.name: Beedrill
data.flavorText: It can take down any opponent with its powerful poison stingers. It sometimes attacks in swarms.

data.name: Butterfree
data.flavorText: It collects honey every day. It rubs honey onto the hairs on its legs to carry it back to its nest.

data.name: Espeon
data.flavorText: By reading air currents, it can predict things such as the weather or its foe's next move.

data.name: Corsola
data.flavorText: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure because of its beauty.

data.name: Eevee
data.flavorText: Its irregularly configured DNA is affected by its surroundings. It evolves if its environment changes.

data.name: Houndour
data.flavorText: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.

data.name: Igglybuff
data.flavorText: It has a very soft body. If it starts to roll, it will bounce all over and be impossible to stop.

data.name: Kakuna
data.flavorText: Although it is a cocoon, it can move a little. It can extend its poison barb if it is attacked.

data.name: Metapod
data.flavorText: Inside the shell, it is soft and weak as it prepares to evolve. It stays motionless in the shell.

data.name: Omastar
data.flavorText: Apparently, it cracked Shellder's shell with its sharp fangs and sucked out the insides.

data.name: Poliwhirl
data.flavorText: The swirl on its belly undulates. Staring at it may gradually cause drowsiness.

data.name: Pupitar
data.flavorText: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.

data.name: Scyther
data.flavorText: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.

data.name: Xatu
data.flavorText: In South America, it is said that its right eye sees the future and its left eye views the past.

data.name: Caterpie
data.flavorText: For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antennae on its head to drive away enemies.

data.name: Dunsparce
data.flavorText: When spotted, this Pokémon escapes backward by furiously boring into the ground with its tail.

data.name: Hoppip
data.flavorText: Its body is so light, it must grip the ground firmly with its feet to keep from being blown away.

data.name: Kabuto
data.flavorText: On rare occasions, some have been found as fossils which they became while hiding on the ocean floor.

data.name: Larvitar
data.flavorText: It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it will fall asleep so it can grow.

data.name: Mareep
data.flavorText: Its fleece grows continually. In the summer, the fleece is fully shed, but it grows back in a week.

data.name: Natu
data.flavorText: It usually forages for food on the ground but may, on rare occasions, hop onto branches to peck at shoots.

data.name: Omanyte
data.flavorText: Revived from an ancient fossil, this Pokémon uses air stored in its shell to sink and rise in water.

data.name: Pineco
data.flavorText: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.

data.name: Poliwag
data.flavorText: Because it is inept at walking on its newly grown legs, it always swims around in water.

data.name: Sentret
data.flavorText: It stands on its tail so it can see a long way. If it spots an enemy, it cries loudly to warn its kind.

data.name: Spinarak
data.flavorText: It spins a web using fine – but durable – thread. It then waits patiently for prey to be trapped.

data.name: Teddiursa
data.flavorText: If it finds honey, its crescent mark glows. It always licks its paws because they are soaked with honey.

data.name: Tyrogue
data.flavorText: It is always bursting with energy. To make itself stronger, it keeps on fighting even if it loses.

data.name: Weedle
data.flavorText: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.

data.name: Wooper
data.flavorText: When it walks around on the ground, it coats its body with a slimy, poisonous film.
